metadata.title: High Resolution Seismic Reflection Profiles Navarin Basin - North Bering Sea, Alaska

creators.name: Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), National Environmental Satellite, Data
Information Service (NESDIS), National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC)

metadata.description:
Approximately 1,600-line km of high-resolution seismic reflection
data are now available in the Navarin Basin, northern Bering Sea.
The data were collected in August 1982 from the U.S. Geological
Survey (USGS) Research Vessel S.P. LEE and deals with seafloor
hazards pertinent to Outer Continental Shelf oil and gas lease
sale activity.  Microfile copies of the seismic records are
available for purchase from the National Geophysical Data Center
(NGDC).  The U.S. Geological Survey, Department of Interior has
provided these data to NGDC for public dissemination.
